div.p:
Clearly, we have a variety of sometimes conflicting interests in oil
                    matters—e.g., to lessen the possibility of being blackmailed or coerced by
                    reducing our dependence on Arab oil and diversifying to other foreign sources;
                    to keep oil prices down so as not to penalize our competitive economic position;
                    to maximize the balance of payments advantages flowing from the U.S. company role in oil; to protect our oil
                    investments; to avoid depleting U.S. reserves;
                    and to reduce our dependence on oil as a fuel.
